gomodel:SYNGO_1028  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig6: CDC10 (SEPT7) in cerebellum, clear labeling of DAB in presynapse (Fig6A), and synaptic terminal plasma membrane in CA3 hippocampus (Fig6C). No quantification is offered.\n\n10/10/2017 Pim\n- The authors state in Fig.6 \"DAB deposition for CDC10 is localized in the presynaptic axon terminals in the granule cell layer. The tips of the axon terminal membrane, rather than around the vesicles, are densely labeled for CDC10.\". Experimental description: M&M: \" We used preembedding immunoperoxidase and immunogold labeling methods. Mouse brains were fixed with PB\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2017-10-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1028" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

